<div type="definition">
<p>QUICKLY AND in a way NOT EXPECTED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most common word for suddenness is hū 忽.</p>
<p>2. Tū 突 and zhà4 乍 "out of the blue" refer to the unforeseen onset of something one has imagined was likely or even possible.</p>
<p>3. Cù 卒 / 猝 refers to the sudden onset of something before it was expected to occur.</p>
<p>4. E@ 俄 and é ér 俄而 refer to the abrupt occurrence of an event of strikingly short duration.</p>
<p>5. Bó 勃 is typically limited in application to the suddenness of the initial emergence of a phenomenon.</p>
        </div>
